and the smaller one is called the circular segment. A more formal mathemati=
cal definition says that:</p>
<p><em>A circular segment is a region bounded by a chord and the arc of a c=
ircle (of less than 180=C2=B0)</em></p>
<p>If it's equal to 180=C2=B0, then it's simply a half circle =E2=80=93 sem=
icircle. According to some definitions, the central angle doesn't need to b=
e smaller than 180=C2=B0 =E2=80=93 in that case, you can say that cutting a=
