iv data-testid=3D"How do I calculate the segment area?-answer" class=3D"css=
-h9evcv e1taq3sq1"><div class=3D"ed4x0bn0 css-48o5u4 e1m4c3o81"><div class=
=3D"textBlock"><p>You can calculate the segment area in three steps:</p>
<ol>
<li>
<p>Determine the <strong>radius of the circle</strong>.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Calculate the <strong>central angle</strong>.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Apply the <strong>segment area formula</strong>:</p>
<p><code>0.5 =C3=97 r=C2=B2 =C3=97 (=CE=B1 =E2=80=93 sin(=CE=B1))</code></p=
>
</li>
</ol></div></div></div><h3 data-testid=3D"What is the segment area if the c=
ircle has a 5 cm radius?" class=3D"css-1ugw61y">What is the segment area if=
